41 CITY OF HICKORY
42 SECTION 5.(a) Section 2.01 of the Charter of the City of Hickory, being Chapter
43 323 of the 1961 Session Laws, as amended by Chapter 404 of the 1967 Session Laws, reads as
44 rewritten:
45 "Sec. 2.01. Composition, Election, and Terms of Mayor and City Council; Time of General
46 Election. (a) The voters of the city shall elect a mayor and six aldermen. council members. The
47 mayor shall be nominated and elected at large. The aldermen council members shall be
48 nominated by wards and elected at large. The candidate from each ward receiving the highest
49 number of votes shall be declared elected. Except as is otherwise provided in this Charter, no two
50 aldermen council members shall be residents of the same ward. All municipal elections shall be
51 nonpartisan.
