1 (b) A general municipal election shall be held on the first Monday in June of 1967, and
2 on the first Monday in June of 1968. In 1970, and biennially thereafter, the general municipal
3 election shall be held on the first Monday in June.Regular municipal elections shall be held at
4 the time of the general election in each even-numbered year. The mayor and aldermen shall be
5 elected on a nonpartisan primary basis and the results determined in accordance with
6 G.S. 163-294. Except as otherwise provided, the elections for the City of Hickory shall be held
7 and conducted in accordance with the uniform municipal election laws in Chapter 163 of the
8 General Statutes.
9 (c) The terms of all council members shall begin at the day and hour prescribed by
10 Section 3.03 of this Charter for the taking of the oath of office, and shall run for a period of four
11 years, except for member's interim terms of three years for the next election of aldermen of the
12 fourth, fifth, and sixth wards. This Section shall apply to elections coming in 1967. Members
13 shall serve until their successors are elected and qualified. In the event that it is not possible
14 otherwise to determine which of two or more persons should be considered a hold-over alderman,
15 decision shall be made by lot between the aldermen who are willing to serve, the lots to be cast
16 under the supervision of the mayor and the remaining qualified aldermen.The mayor shall be
17 elected for a term of four years. The terms of office of council members shall be four-year
18 staggered terms."
19 SECTION 5.(b) No municipal elections shall be conducted in the City of Hickory
20 in 2027. The terms of office for the three Council members in the City of Hickory serving on the
