29 SECTION 6.(a) Section 3 of the Charter of the Town of Long View, being Chapter
30 430 of the Private Laws of 1907, as amended by Chapter 131 of the Private Laws of 1929,
31 Chapter 789 of the 1955 Session Laws, and Motion of Town Board of Aldermen Meeting on
32 January 3, 1978, reads as rewritten:
33 "Sec. 3. Town Elections.
34 (a) The governing body for the Town of Long View shall consist of a mayor and five
35 aldermen. The mayor shall be nominated and elected by the voters at large for a four-year term
36 and shall serve until a successor is elected and qualified. Each ward of the Town of Long View
37 shall be represented on the board of aldermen by one alderman, who must be a resident of that
38 ward and nominated and elected by that ward. The aldermen shall serve four-year staggered terms
39 and until their successors are elected and qualified.
40 The Town of Long View shall be divided into five wards as follows:
41 …
42 (b) Regular municipal elections shall be held at the time of the general election in each
43 even-numbered year. The mayor and aldermen shall be elected on a nonpartisan plurality basis
44 and the results determined in accordance with G.S. 163-292. Except as otherwise provided, the
45 elections for the Town of Long View shall be held and conducted in accordance with the uniform
46 municipal election laws in Chapter 163 of the General Statutes."
47 SECTION 6.(b) No municipal elections shall be conducted in the Town of Long
